{
  "text": "where S VSC.rate (n) is the rated apparent power of the VSC HVDC connected to the n-th bus. Note that conversion loss of a VSC HVDC is ignored, because the input variables of controller are active and reactive power output at the inverter side. However, for future work, the conversion loss of VSC should be considered for solving overall optimization problems, including a DC system. The reactive power output of the LCC, Q LCC , is different from the VSC, and cannot be regulated independent of the active power, P LCC [CITATION_1] . As conversion loss of LCC is less than 1% in general, the loss can be ignored [CITATION_2] . Thus, Q LCC can be presented as:",
